<div class='section_small'>
	<h3>Improvements and Future Considerations</h3>
	<p>Based on our user evaluations, there are a couple of areas that we would need to improve on. Most importantly is the flow and speed of using our application. Most users found that the functionality of our app to be useful, but some functions, such as finding the closest washroom, took too many steps. Another area of improvement needed is the map routing feature. Some icons on the map were not discernable by users, and others felt the map was too cluttered when the route was plotted. The refinement of semantics and categorization of certain items are also required to improve overall usability.</p>
	<p>When conducting our user evaluations, participants were generally positive with our application. Over 90% of our participants said they would use our app. Many of them said they would use it if the application notifies them of current sales in stores, with one person mentioning that she would continually use the app if it offered discounts or coupons of some sort. If we were to continue developing this application, we would look into implementing this feature in cooperation with store managers.</p>
